ord(): Returns the integer (ASCII/Unicode) value for a given single character
print(ord('A'))  # Output: 65
print(ord('a'))  # Output: 97
print(ord('!'))  # Output: 33

chr(): Returns the character corresponding to a given integer ASCII value
print(chr(65))   # Output: A
print(chr(97))   # Output: a
print(chr(33))   # Output: !
